# Recovery Point checksum file example
#
# This file is a placeholder that demonstrates the generated output expected
# in a completed Recovery Point.
#
# The Recovery Point automation creates the real file as:
#
#   checksums.sha256
#
# Each generated line contains:
#
#   <SHA-256 checksum>  <relative file path>
#
# Example:
#
# d2d2d2d2d2d2d2d2d2d2d2d2d2d2d2d2d2d2d2d2d2d2d2d2d2d2d2d2d2d2d2d2  ./RP_MANIFEST.md
# a1a1a1a1a1a1a1a1a1a1a1a1a1a1a1a1a1a1a1a1a1a1a1a1a1a1a1a1a1a1a1a1  ./SYSTEM_RECOVERY_MANUAL.md
#
# Do not use the example checksum values for verification.
# The real values are generated from the files contained in the Recovery Point.
